OL,3,CThe only British brothers to die on
OL,4,Cthe beaches of Normandy
OL,6,FCarole Wheeler's father Colour
OL,7,FSergeant Davis of the Fifth Battalion
OL,8,FKings Regiment in landed on Sword
OL,9,FBeach on 6 June 1944.
OL,11,FWhile his brother, Lieutenant Davis,
OL,12,Fof the West Yorkshire regiment, was
OL,13,Fplaced further up the coast on Gold
OL,14,FBeach.
OL,16,FNorman was originally meant to return
OL,17,Fhome on , but his wife was later told
OL,18,Fhe had gone back to help an injured
OL,19,Ffriend.
