OL,3,CThe only British brothers to die on
OL,4,Cthe beaches of Normandy
OL,6,F"I was in bed one evening my mother
OL,7,Fheard me talking to somebody, so she
OL,8,Fwent upstairs to see who I was talking
OL,9,Fto," she said.
OL,11,F"She went in and she said 'who are you
OL,12,Ftalking to?' and I said 'Daddy', and
OL,13,Fshe thought, 'oh okay' and realised
OL,14,Fthat my father had died sometime ago."
OL,16,FThe brothers were 28 and 24 when they
OL,17,Fdied, and both are buried in
OL,18,FHermonville Cemetery, two miles from
OL,19,Fwhere they were killed.
